This paper focuses on the interaction between human and artificial intelligence in the context of building personalized recommendation systems. It proposes a novel metric for evaluating the strength of the cyclic relationship between the two, which is relevant to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of EEG signals as a measure of explanatory efficacy, which is relevant to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories.
